cmpReviews: I really enjoyed working with everyone at NYC Build It Back. Great job culture and the people who I worked with were very friendly and very professional. Each day at work, I worked on a project that helped a victim of Hurricane Sandy. I liked working with the management because they were approachable and were open to suggestion. I learned how to use CMS on the computer. The hardest part of this job was leaving due to my contract as temporary ended.
